Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses resource management in large-scale distributed systems, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The DIANA scheduling algorithm and its queue management system are designed to be network-aware, which is relevant to this sub-category. 
3. cs.Distributed Systems - The paper discusses scheduling in distributed systems, which is the main focus of this sub-category. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a self-organizing resource management system, which is relevant to this sub-category. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the design and implementation of a scheduling algorithm and queue management system, which are relevant to this sub-category.
